  "elapsed_s": 27.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Auschwitz, I met a friend, a girlfriend of a very good friend of mine, who by this time had a job of-- in the Unterkunft, which Unterkunft was the place where you selected the clothing.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was able to get seven jobs for seven girls, and I was one of them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And no-- I was only working there for just a few days when I was-- got terribly ill with typhus, the very typhus that I had until after liberation-- until after I was liberated.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How I survived, I do not know, because a doctor prisoner said to my sisters that, at home, with the best of care, I would die.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I survived this, but I was young and healthy yet.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And after being in Auschwitz and trying to outmaneuver Mengele's selections, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and my sister working at the Unter-- actually, I was to work  in the Unterkunft, but because I got so ill, I no longer had the strength to go.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So this girl, at the peril of her life, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] took my sister in in my stead.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was not supposed to do that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Any infraction on the holy writ and the holy laws of Hitler was punishable by death, yet she took it upon herself to sneak in my sister, because I had fever perhaps as high as 105.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't know how anyone can survive it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the only way to quench my thirst standing in the [GERMAN] was that  that little rusty can that some of us had on a string on our-- that was our dish, our-- our china, our porcelain dish.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
